{
  "texts": [
    "During training, these models learn to map the input to an appropriate explanation, clarifying why the given statement conflicts with commonsense.",
    "Generative approaches, on the other hand, use auto-regressive pre-trained language models (PLMs), such as GPT-2 [15], to produce explanations.",
    "Instead of directly learning input-output mappings, these methods [16][17][18] create prompts to guide the model's generation of suitable explanations.",
    "This approach leverages the inherent generative abilities of language models, tailoring their outputs to meet the task's requirements.Recent advancements in large language models have led to substantial improvements in natural language processing (NLP), with these models achieving state-of-the-art performance on a wide range of tasks [19].",
    "Concurrently, the NLP community has gradually shifted its focus from traditional supervised learning methods to leverage prompting with LLMs."
  ]
}